<h1>{{ company_name }}{% trans %}Privacy Policy{% endtrans %}</h1>
<h3>{{ company_name }}</h3>
<h3>{% trans %}Last updated{% endtrans %}: {{ last_updated }}</h3>

<hr />

<p>
{% trans company_name=company_name %}{{ company_name }} (“we” or “us” or “our”) respects the privacy of our users (“user” or “you”). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, retain, disclose, and safeguard your information whenever you access or use in any manner any {{ company_name }} application, product, service, feature, technology, content, or website (collectively, “Services”). By registering or signing up for a {{ company_name }} account, including through a computer or mobile device, you accept the terms of this Privacy Policy. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully.{% endtrans %}
</p>
<ul>
<li><b>{% trans %}IF YOU DO NOT AGREE WITH THE TERMS OF THIS PRIVACY POLICY, PLEASE DO NOT ACCESS THE SERVICES.{% endtrans %}</b></li>
</ul>

<p>
{% trans %}We reserve the right to make changes to this Privacy Policy at any time and for any reason. We will alert you about any changes by updating the “Last updated” date of this Privacy Policy.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<p>
{% trans %}You are encouraged to periodically review this Privacy Policy to stay informed of updates. You will be deemed to have been made aware of, will be subject to, and will be deemed to have accepted the changes in any revised Privacy Policy by your continued use of the Services after the date such revised Privacy Policy is posted.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<p>
{% trans %}This Privacy Policy does not apply to the third-party online/mobile store from which you install the Services or make payments, including any in-game virtual items, which may also collect and use data about you.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<p>
{% trans %}We are not responsible for any of the data collected by any such third party.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h2>1.{% trans %}Important Information{% endtrans %}</h2>
<h3>1.1.{% trans %}Changes to this Privacy Policy{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time by posting a new version online. You should check this page occasionally to review any changes. If we make any material changes we will notify you by posting the revised Privacy Policy on our Online Store and, if you order from our store, providing notice through the Notification app in the {{ company_name }} Store Admin. This helps you to always be aware of what information we collect, how we use it and under what circumstances, if any, it is disclosed. Your continued use of the Online Store, the online store services, and/or continued provision of Personal Information to us will be subject to the terms of the then-current Privacy Policy.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>1.2.{% trans %}Contact Us{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans store_email=store_email, full_address=full_address %}If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our treatment of the information you provide us, please write to us by email at {{ store_email }} or by mail to {{ full_address }}, Attn: Privacy.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h2>2.{% trans company_name=company_name  %}Use of the Online Store by {{ company_name }} and our Customers{% endtrans %}</h2>
<h3>2.1.{% trans company_name=company_name %}The {{ company_name }} Online Store{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans company_name=company_name %}Our online store allows any company (or person) that uses it (our customers and {{ company_name }} itself) to order the products available in the store.{% endtrans %}
</p>
<p>
{% trans %}Customer has two ways of providing information to us:{% endtrans %}
</p>
<ul>
  <li>1.{% trans %}Registering to our page{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>2.{% trans %}Ordering products from us{% endtrans %}</li>
</ul>
<p>
{% trans %}This, voluntarely given, information, which is stored and managed on our service providers' servers, is used to ensure the services can be run and ensures we are able to provide our service.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>2.2.{% trans company_name=company_name %}Use by {{ company_name }}{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}Information that we collect and manage using this Online Store belongs to us and is used, disclosed and protected according to this Privacy Policy.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>2.3.{% trans %}Use by Our Customers{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans company_name=company_name, store_email=store_email %}{{ company_name }} collects information under the direction of its customers, and has no direct relationship with the individuals whose Personal Information it processes. If you would no longer like to be contacted by us, please contact us directly at <a href="mailto:{{ store_email }}">{{ store_email }}</a>. We may transfer Personal Information to companies that help us provide our service. Transfers to subsequent third parties are covered by the service agreements with them.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>2.4. "{% trans %}Sensitive Information{% endtrans %}"</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}This refers to credit or debit card numbers, personal financial account information, Social Security numbers, passport numbers, driver's license numbers or similar personal identifiers, racial or ethnic origin, physical or mental health condition or information, or other employment, financial or health information.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h2>3.{% trans %}Information We Collect{% endtrans %}</h2>
<h3>3.1.{% trans %}When You Visit our Online Store{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}You are free to explore the Online Store without providing any Personal Information about yourself. When you order from our Online Store or register to the Online Store, we request that you provide Personal Information about yourself, and we collect Navigational Information.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>3.2. "{% trans %}Personal Information{% endtrans %}"</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}This refers to any information that you voluntarily submit to us and that identifies you personally, including contact information, such as your name, e-mail address, company name, address, phone number, and other information about yourself or your business.{% endtrans %}
</p>
<p>
{% trans %}Personal Information can also include information about any transactions, both free and paid, that you enter into on the Online Store, and information about you that is available on the internet, such as from Facebook, LinkedIn, Twitter and Google, or publicly available information that we acquire from service providers.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>3.3. "{% trans %}Navigational Information{% endtrans %}"</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}This refers to information about your computer and your visits to this website such as your IP address, geographical location, browser type, referral source, length of visit and pages viewed. Please see the "Navigation Information" section below.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>3.4.{% trans %}Payment Information{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}We collect and process payment information from you when you order from the Online Store, including credit cards numbers and billing information, using third party PCI-compliant service providers. The payment card information is not saved into our servers.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>3.5.{% trans %}Information About Children{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans store_email=store_email %}The Online Store are not intended for or targeted at children under 13, and we do not knowingly or intentionally collect information about children under 13. If you believe that we have collected information about a child under 13, please contact us at {{ store_email }}, so that we may delete the information.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h2>4.{% trans %}How We Use Information We Collect{% endtrans %}</h2>
<h3>4.1.{% trans %}Compliance with Our Privacy Policy{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}We use the information we collect only in compliance with this Privacy Policy.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.2.{% trans %}We Never Sell Personal Information{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}We will never sell your Personal Information to any third party.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.3.{% trans %}Use of Personal Information{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans store_email=store_email %}In addition to the uses identified elsewhere in this Privacy Policy, we may use your Personal Information to: (a) improve your browsing experience by personalizing the Online Store and to improve the Online Store; (b) send information to you which we think may be of interest to you by post, email, or other means; (c) send you marketing communications relating to our business or the businesses of carefully-selected third parties which we think may be of interest to you, and (d) provide other companies with statistical information about our users -- but this information will not be used to identify any individual user. We may, from time to time, contact you on behalf of external business partners about a particular offering that may be of interest to you. In those cases, we do not transfer your unique Personal Information to the third party. In addition, we may share data with trusted partners to contact you based on your request to receive such communications, help us perform statistical analysis, or provide customer support. Such third parties are prohibited from using your Personal Information except for these purposes, and they are required to maintain the confidentiality of your information. If you do not want us to share your personal information with these companies, contact us at {{ store_email }}.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.4.{% trans %}Use of Navigational Information{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans company_name=company_name %}We use Navigational Information to operate and improve the Online Store. We may also use Navigational Information alone or in combination with Personal Information to provide you with personalized information about {{ company_name }}.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.5.{% trans %}Customer Testimonials and Comments{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}We post customer testimonials and comments on our Online Store, which may contain Personal Information. We obtain each customer's consent via email prior to posting the customer's name and testimonial.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.6.{% trans %}Use of Credit Card Information{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}We use a third-party service provider to manage credit card processing. This service provider is not permitted to store, retain, or use information you provide except for the sole purpose of credit card processing on our behalf.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.7.{% trans %}Service Providers{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}We employ other companies and people to provide services to visitors to our Online Store, our customers, and users of the Online Store and may need to share your information with them to provide information, products or services to you. Examples may include removing repetitive information from prospect lists, analyzing data, providing marketing assistance, processing credit card payments, supplementing the information you provide us in order to provide you with better service, and providing customer service. In all cases where we share your information with such agents, we explicitly require the agent to acknowledge and adhere to our privacy and customer data handling policies.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.8.{% trans %}Security of your Personal Information{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}We use a variety of security technologies and procedures to help protect your Personal Information from unauthorized access, use or disclosure. We secure the Personal Information you provide on computer servers in a controlled, secure environment, protected from unauthorized access, use or disclosure. When sensitive Personal Information (such as a credit card number and/or geo-location data) is collected on our Online Store and/or transmitted to other websites, it is protected through the use of encryption, such as the Secure Socket Layer (SSL) protocol.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<p>
{% trans store_email=store_email %}If you have any questions about the security of your Personal Information, you can contact us at {{ store_email }}.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.9.{% trans %}Social Media Features{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}Our Online Store may include Social Media Features, such as the Facebook Like button and Widgets, such as the Share This button or interactive mini-programs that run on our sites. These features may collect your IP address, which page you are visiting on our sites, and may set a cookie to enable the feature to function properly. Social Media Features and Widgets are either hosted by a third party or hosted directly on our Online Store. This Privacy Policy does not apply to these features.{% endtrans %}
</p>
<p>
{% trans %}Your interactions with these features are governed by the privacy policy and other policies of the companies providing them.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.10.{% trans %}External Websites{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}Our Online Store provide links to other websites. We do not control, and are not responsible for, the content or practices of these other websites. Our provision of such links does not constitute our endorsement of these other websites, their content, their owners, or their practices. This Privacy Policy does not apply to these other websites, which are subject to any privacy and other policies they may have.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.12.{% trans %}Retention of Personal Information{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}We retain Personal Information that you provide us as long as we consider it potentially useful in contacting you about the Online Store or our other services, or as needed to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes and enforce our agreements, and then we securely delete the information. We will delete this information from the servers at an earlier date if you so request, as described in "Opting Out and Unsubscribing" below. If we terminate the use of the Online Store, then we will provide you with access to all information stored for the Online Store, including any Personal Information provided by you. After termination, we may, unless legally prohibited, delete all customer information, including your Personal Information, from the Online Store.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.13.{% trans %}International Transfer of Information{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}To facilitate our possible global operations, we may transfer and access Personal Information from around the world, including the United States. This Privacy Policy shall apply even if we transfer Personal Information to other countries.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.14.{% trans %}Corporate Events{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans company_name=company_name %}If we (or our assets) are acquired by another company, whether by merger, acquisition, bankruptcy or otherwise, that company would receive all information gathered by {{ company_name }} on the Online Store. In this event, you will be notified via email and/or a prominent notice on our website, of any change in ownership, uses of your Personal Information, and choices you may have regarding your Personal Information.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>4.15.{% trans %}Compelled Disclosure{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}We reserve the right to use or disclose your Personal Information if required by law or if we reasonably believe that use or disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, protect your safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or comply with a law, court order, or legal process.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h2>5.{% trans %}Navigational Information{% endtrans %}</h2>
<h3>5.1.{% trans %}Cookies{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}{{ company_name }} and its partners use cookies or similar technologies to analyze trends, administer the website, track users’ movements around the website, and to gather demographic information about our user base as a whole.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<p>
{% trans %}We use "cookies" to help you personalize your online shopping experience. A cookie is a text file that is placed on your hard disk by a Web server. Cookies are not used to run programs or deliver viruses to your computer. Cookies are uniquely assigned to you, and can only be read by a Web server in the domain that issued the cookie to you. One of the primary purposes of cookies is to provide a convenience feature to save you time. The purpose of a cookie is to tell the Web server that you have returned to a specific page.{% endtrans %}
</p>
<p>
{% trans %}For example, if you personalize pages on our Online Store, or register for the Online Store, a cookie helps us to recall your specific information on subsequent visits. When you return to the same Website, the information you previously provided can be retrieved, so you can easily use the customized features.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<p>
{% trans company_name=company_name %}You have the ability to accept or decline cookies. Most Web browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies if you prefer. If you choose to decline cookies, you may not be able to fully experience the interactive features of the {{ company_name }} Online Store you visit. {{ company_name }} keeps track of the Online Store and pages you visit within {{ company_name }}, in order to determine what portion of the {{ company_name }} Online Store is the most popular or most used. This data is used to deliver customized content and promotions within the {{ company_name }} Online Store to customers whose behavior indicates that they are interested in a particular subject area.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>5.2.{% trans %}Log Files{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans company_name=company_name %}We may collect demographic information, such as your ZIP code, age, gender, preferences, interests and favorites using log files that are not associated with your name or other personal information. There is also information about your computer hardware and software that is automatically collected by us. This information can include: your IP address, browser type, domain names, internet service provider (ISP), the files viewed on our site (e.g., HTML pages, graphics, etc.), operating system, clickstream data, access times and referring website addresses. This information is used by {{ company_name }} for the operation of the Online Store, to maintain quality of the Online Store, and to provide general statistics regarding use of the {{ company_name }} Online Store. For these purposes, we do link this automatically-collected data to Personal Information such as name, email address, address, and phone number.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>5.3.{% trans %}Flash Cookies and Other Third Party Tracking Technologies{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans company_name=company_name %}The Adobe Flash Player (and similar applications) use technology to remember settings, preferences and usage similar to browser cookies but these are managed through a different interface than the one provided by your Web browser. This technology creates locally stored objects that are often referred to as "Flash cookies." {{ company_name }} may create pages on the Online Store that employ Adobe Flash cookies. {{ company_name }} does not have access or control over our customers' Flash cookies, but you may access your Flash management tools from Adobe's web site directly here.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<p>
{% trans company_name=company_name %}Similarly, we may create pages using the {{ company_name }} Online Store that use technology from tracking utility companies, such as cookies and web beacons. If we decide use these technologies, we will update this Privacy Policy to reflect these changes.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h2>6.{% trans %}Opting Out and Unsubscribing{% endtrans %}</h2>
<h3>6.1.{% trans %}Reviewing, Correcting and Removing Your Personal Information{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans company_name=company_name %}Upon request {{ company_name }} will provide you with information about whether we hold any of your Personal Information. If you provide us with your Personal Information, you have the following rights with respect to that information:{% endtrans %}
</p>

<ul>
  <li>{% trans %}To review the user information that you have supplied to us{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>{% trans %}To request that your user information be removed from any solicitation list that we use{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>{% trans %}To request that your user information be deleted from our records{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>{% trans company_name=company_name %}To opt out of being solicited by {{ company_name }} or third parties{% endtrans %}</li>
</ul>

<p>
{% trans store_email=store_email, full_address=full_address %}To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at {{ store_email }} or by mail to {{ full_address }}, Attention: Privacy. We will respond to your request to change, correct, or delete your information within a reasonable timeframe and notify you of the action we have taken.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>6.2.{% trans %}Anti-Spam Policy{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans %}Our Acceptable Use Policy, applies to us and to our customers and, among other things, prohibits use of the Online Store to send unsolicited commercial email in violation of applicable laws, and requires the inclusion in every email sent using the Online Store of an "opt-out" mechanism and other required information. We require all of our customers to agree to adhere to the Acceptable Use Policy at all times, and any violations of the Acceptable Use Policy by a customer can result in immediate suspension or termination of the Online Store.{% endtrans %}
</p>

<h3>6.3.{% trans %}To Unsubscribe From Our Communications{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>
{% trans full_address=full_address, store_email=store_email %}You may unsubscribe from our marketing communications by clicking on the "unsubscribe" link located on the bottom of our e-mails, or by sending us email us at {{ store_email }}, or by sending us postal mail to {{ full_address }}, Attention: Privacy. Customers cannot opt out of receiving transactional emails related to their account with us or the Online Store.{% endtrans %}
</p>
